		<div class="entry-content">
			<p>Without change, things stagnate. When things stagnate, they risk becoming
obsolete. Change for the sake of change is inefficient and just spins around
chasing its own tail - the change should have a purpose. Therefore: to avoid
risk of becoming obsolete, make purposeful changes.</p>
<p>That said, here is some purposeful change: a revamped incarnation of my blog.</p>
<p>The <strong>old posts were cleaned up</strong> and many were thrown away. I kept
the ones which were still interesting to me. You can find the old posts in the
Old-category at the top.</p>
<p>Also, the old "Zenburn updated" posts are gone - any future updates will be
reflected at the <a href="https://github.com/jnurmine/Zenburn">Zenburn repository in Github</a>.</p>
<p>Also, due to massive amounts of spam, the comment system has moved to Disqus. I
have kept the old comments only at the <a href="/zenburnpage/">Zenburn page</a> since the
comments are valuable to a number of people.</p>
